{
  "answer": "**1. In-Depth User Understanding:** Recognizing the believer's profound need to comprehend the unseen, the Prophet Muhammad addressed the question regarding the timing of the Last Hour by clarifying that the one being asked knows no more than the inquirer [1, 2]. \n\n**2. Robust and Enduring Framework:** To build a steadfast and resilient theological foundation, the Prophet established a clear awareness of the future by explicitly detailing specific, observable portents to signal the approach of the Hour [1, 2].\n\n**3. Elegant and Lucid Presentation:** The narrations elegantly and lucidly present these signs, explicitly stating that the Hour will be marked by a slave-girl giving birth to her master [2, 3]. Furthermore, it will be signaled when naked, barefooted shepherds of black camels begin to boast and fiercely compete with one another in constructing exceptionally high buildings [2-4].\n\n**4. Seamless and Accessible Experience:** By providing these vivid and physical descriptions, the teachings offer a highly accessible framework that seamlessly allows believers to recognize shifting worldly conditions and spiritually prepare for the Last Day [1, 2].",
